2026-04-16 07:51:42 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['control module 1', 'control module 2', 'control module 3', 'control module 4', 'control module 5', 'control module 6', 'control module 7', 'control module 8'] hypothesis_explanation="The indicator LEDs (and possibly their resistors) in all control modules (1–8) have been physically removed. In the circuit design, these LEDs and their associated resistors are needed to provide continuity between the input and output terminals of each control module when its switch is closed. If the LEDs (and series resistors) are removed, it creates an open circuit at each control module, interrupting the series current needed to illuminate the load (lamp). Thus, even with all switches 'on', current cannot pass through the module locations, so neither the control module indicators nor the final lamp can turn on. The root cause is the missing components in every control module."
