2026-04-16 07:52:13 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['all control module indicator LEDs'] hypothesis_explanation='The visual inspection confirmed that all indicator LEDs in the control modules are physically missing and cannot be replaced. In this circuit, the path through each control module is only complete if the switch is closed and the LED-resistor branch forms a shunt between the two terminals. With the LEDs entirely removed from the circuit (open holders), each control module leaves an open circuit across itself, breaking the series path from the power supply to the load. This explains why there is no voltage or current at the load module, and neither the main lamp nor the load indicator lamp will illuminate. The absence of all the control module indicator LEDs is the root cause of the system failure.'
